OL,7,FLabour MS Hefin David was trying to
OL,8,Fheckle over the former leader of Welsh
OL,9,FLabour as he continued.
OL,11,FEducation secretary Lynne Neagle
OL,12,Fresponded by saying: "With respect I
OL,13,Fthink I have very clearly set out my
OL,14,Freasons for making this decision
OL,15,Ftoday."
OL,17,FDrakeford could be seen trying to
OL,18,Fintervene, to which Ms Neagle said:
OL,19,F"Can you let me finish, because I let
OL,20,Fyou finish, I didn't say a word whilst
OL,21,Fyou were speaking."
